2017 cumulative results (Q1,2,3) 

Output 1:

1.1) 3 Federal states agreed upon charters and approved constitutions;
1.2) 4 inclusive mediation processes were supported and led by IRA/FGS. These include, Jowhar mediation process for Adalle, Galkaio Peace mediation efforts, Kismayo returnees IDPs and host community reconciliation;
1.3) 3.68% (38% women) of the total staffs (paid and unpaid) are trained in conflict management and community problem solving at SWS and GSS. 11.74% (38% women) of the total staffs (paid and unpaid) are trained in conflict management and community problem solving at SWS and GSS;

Output 2:

2.1) 3 technical advisors (M:2, W:1) and 3 Interns (M:2, W:1) were provided to BFC to assist in policy development and implementation (disaggregated by sex);
2.2) All 9 (and 100%) of BFC members with access to basic equipment, disaggregated by sex; 
2.3) BFC Strategic Plan/Framework for the period 2016-20 has been drafted and confirmed;
2.4) 10TAs (M:7, W:2) and 10 interns (M:7, W:3) were provided to MoIFA, and 2 TAs (M:2), and 1 Intern (W:1) were provided to OPM to assist in policy development and implementation on federalism process (disaggregated by sex);
2.5) 100% of MOIFA units have received office equipment;
2.6) 4 consultations with regions and emerging states convened and facilitated by FGS/MOIFA; 

Output 3:

3.2)  10 new or rehabilitated infrastructure projects were undertaken for the Interim State Administrations (ISAs) 

Output 4:

4.2) 14 (M:11, W:3) technical advisors/officers, and 17 Interns (M:11, W:6) were supported at the Interim State Administrations (JSS, SWS, GSS) for organization development and planning process (disaggregated by sex). The distribution of human resources as per state include JSS: 3 TA/Os (2M:1W), and 7 interns (5M:2W); SWS: 8 TA/Os (7M:1W); GSS: 3 TA/Os (2M:1W), and 10 interns (6M:4W)
4.3) 24.6% (M:255, W:79) of staff members (total 1,357) of beneficiary state ministries/agencies that receive trainings on core of g

