description.narrative:
1- Framework of Constitutional Review Process agreed by end of May 2015; Master plan of Constitutional Review Process drafted and circulated amongst national and international partners by end June 2015; Master Plan agreed by end of Dec 2015. 

2-Regional Conferences held no later than August 2015; Each regional conference presents recommendations for the National Conference; National Conference outlines main consensus reached and agrees on recommendations to be included in the revised constitution.

3 - Civic Education Plan finalised and agreed byby end June 2015; Website for the Constitutional review process functioning by end of July 2015; At least one media civic education activity launched by August 2015, at National and Regional level; At least 1 specific civic education activity for women undertaken until September 2015, in more than one region; At least one specific civic education activity for youth undertaken until September 2015, in more than one region;

4- Office space set up in first 2 months of PIP initiation; All support staff and constitutional experts hired in the 2 months of PIP; At least one thematic session and/or one training session conducted each month, per institution; At least one monthly joint OC/ICRIC outreach activity conducted between Jul-Nov; ICRIC's Methodology of work developed and agreed by end of June 2015.

5 - All staff hired by end of June 2015; At least one outreach activity per month conducted in Puntland;

comment.narrative:
1.Draft MoU between National institutions exists; division of labor between UN and other international implementers not defined; 
2. One Vision 2016 conference undertaken in 2013; 
3. No civic education activity undertaken until 2015; 
4. Capacities of national institutions limited; 
5. Limited or no capacity of sub-national institutions; additional sub-national institutions to be established;

description.narrative:
1. Set of committees established by Parliament with defined functions; Committees able to provide effective oversight of laws and policy; Parliament effectively engaged in budget cycle, incl. undertaking oversight of key ministries expenditures.  

2. # of members of Parliamentary leadership supported to manage the business of the Chamber; Staff capacity increased to provide support services to Office of the Speaker & MPs; NFP, Somaliland and Puntland Strategic Plans inclusively developed and implementation progressed; Pre/Post assessment by contracted company indicates improvements against HACT criteria; 

3. Improved understanding of key Public target groups of the role of Parliament and MPs; Parliaments supported to develop and implement communication and outreach strategies with a particular focus on youth, women and marginalized groups.

comment.narrative:
1. No Committees established in NFP; No public hearings held by NFP Committees; No Legal Research Unit and legislative drafting capacity in NFP; Very limited capacity and experience to provide oversight of Executive; Limited parliamentary oversight of the Budget. 

2. NFP Parliamentary Leadership have limited capacity; 45 young graduates were hired in 2013; No Strategic Plan for the Somaliland or Puntland Parliaments; Capacity assessments showed significant risks with regard to parliaments’ financial / operational abilities (HACT criteria); 

3. Limited understanding by public of role of Parliament in national democracy; No outreach and communication strategies in Parliaments. Very limited outreach to population

1. NFP Budget committee producing 1 reports with recommendations for the Executive; 
2. Training provided to 20 members of staff of Office of the Speaker, and Administration, Finance and IT departments; 
3. Construction of security perimeter completed by end 2016
4. 100% of recommendations re high/significant risks implemented; 
5. Minimum 2 trainings on outreach and communication held.

description.narrative:
- Framework/Timeline of Constitution Review;
- Review Process agreed by end of August 2017;
- Master plan of Constitutional Review Process drafted and circulated amongst national and international partners by end August 2017;
- Project document (draft) is complete; reflects the inputs of all key stakeholders; and is ready for approval.
